title: Places to Study at The University of Minnesota
name: Places to Study at The University of Minnesota

properties.name: Coffman Memorial Union
properties.description: This is a very comfortable place to study, although sometimes it can be a little busy and noisy.

properties.name: Northrop Mall
properties.description: This area is a perfect spot to study outside when it's a nice day out.

properties.name: Walter Library
properties.description: This is a quiet place to study, with lots of private study rooms.  Sometimes it can be crowded.

properties.name: West Bank Bridge Area
properties.description: This area can be a little loud sometimes, but there are plenty of tables to study at.

properties.name: Wilson Library
properties.description: This is an extremely quiet and comfortable place to study. It is never crowded.
